You know that it's not my style.

257
00:17:03,059 --> 00:17:05,495
What is it? Did another show call?

258
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:07,495
Why on earth not?

259
00:17:08,299 --> 00:17:09,699
You've got the looks.

260
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,038
And you're more than qualified.

261
00:17:11,039 --> 00:17:12,808
And you are eloquent beyond this world.

262
00:17:12,809 --> 00:17:14,509
Why won't you star on TV shows?

263
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:16,305
So that you can die in frustration.

264
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,775
Didn't you know?

265
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,509
And most importantly, I don't want to.

266
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:22,075
I don't care about that.

267
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:25,319
Let me be blunt. Did your family
take out a private loan?

268
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:27,219
Or do you have a lot of ex-girlfriends

269
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:28,419
who want to kill you?

270
00:17:28,420 --> 00:17:29,459
Hey.

271
00:17:29,460 --> 00:17:30,585
Yes?

272
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:34,285
You're a mind reader.

273
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:36,725
You sure are.

274
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:38,925
I'll take care of that. Don't worry.

275
00:17:38,970 --> 00:17:40,899
Pick me up at the airport this evening.
Don't be late.

276
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:43,369
Since you're going down there,
take a day off.

277
00:17:43,370 --> 00:17:45,209
Go to a cafe by Woljeong Beach

278
00:17:45,210 --> 00:17:46,669
and have a cup of caramel macchiato.

279
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:48,675
If you spot a single woman,
why don't you...

280
00:17:48,910 --> 00:17:49,939
[ Kim Hae-kyong ]

281
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:51,509
- Give her a card, you know.
- No.

282
00:17:51,510 --> 00:17:54,079
If you don't want to be on TV,
you should at least date someone.

283
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:55,549
This research paper says single people

284
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:57,019
die earlier than people who are obese.

285
00:17:57,020 --> 00:17:58,215
Did you know that or not?

286
00:17:58,290 --> 00:17:59,419
Really?

287
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,515
Yes.

288
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:06,089
I'll start binge-eating as of today
to outlive those single people.

289
00:18:06,090 --> 00:18:07,225
I'm off now.

290
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:14,799
He won't even let me have anything.

291
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,135
He's annoyingly logical.

292
00:18:16,170 --> 00:18:17,295
Darn it.

293
00:18:18,670 --> 00:18:20,505
You're really not going to call him first?

294
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:22,939
Of course not. It will be a surprise.

295
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:24,909
My gosh, it's making me nervous.

296
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:26,579
From the vibe I get from him,

297
00:18:26,580 --> 00:18:29,175
it looks like he's going to propose.

298
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:31,389
What? Really? No way.

299
00:18:31,390 --> 00:18:33,615
Are you feeling it this time?

300
00:18:37,890 --> 00:18:38,985
[ Yeong-dong ]

301
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:45,295
[ Out of the blue, he sent me
a photo of a ring last week. ]

302
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,225
He'll propose for sure.

303
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,769
So I asked what it was for.

304
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:52,665
He told me his friend asked if the ring
looked okay for a proposal.

305
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:56,535
But he had no clue if it was good,
so he wanted to know what I thought.

306
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,805
That's cute.

307
00:18:59,710 --> 00:19:02,879
Hey, so are you going to run a cafe
in Jeju Island as a couple

308
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,415
and live like Lee Hyo-ri?

309
00:19:04,420 --> 00:19:06,245
I guess so.

310
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:09,785
I'll be back with my ring right here.

311
00:19:09,990 --> 00:19:11,625
- Right here.
- Here.

312
00:19:13,230 --> 00:19:16,555
- See you.
- Okay, see you soon.

313
00:19:21,540 --> 00:19:22,735
What a lucky brat.

314
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,275
Hey, Yeong-dong.

315
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:34,545
It is currently May 4, 1:30 p.m.

316
00:19:35,020 --> 00:19:36,819
Three hours before landing in Jeju Island.

317
00:19:36,820 --> 00:19:41,015
You have no idea I'm on my way right now.

318
00:19:41,390 --> 00:19:44,859
I'm recording this because I have a hunch
we're going to have

319
00:19:44,860 --> 00:19:46,255
a historic moment together.

320
00:19:46,430 --> 00:19:49,555
I'm going to show this
to our future kids too.

321
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:52,465
I'm blushing.

322
00:19:52,830 --> 00:19:54,225
Enjoy your trip.

323
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:58,905
Here.

324
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:04,775
I'm checking in now.

325
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,949
I hope I get a front seat
so I can stretch my legs.

326
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:09,919
Ms. Woo Do-hee, we've upgraded your seat
to business class.

327
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,045
- Enjoy your trip.
- No way.

328
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:15,915
Thank you.
I've got a good feeling about this.

329
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:19,955
I feel like the world is helping me
and blessing us.

330
00:20:20,260 --> 00:20:23,125
I'm feeling good even before departing.
Right, Yeong-dong?

331
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:26,265
I'm boarding business class. Let's go.

332
00:20:30,170 --> 00:20:31,265
No way.

333
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,705
This is so cool! I love it.

334
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:39,305
It's a whole new world.

335
00:20:39,980 --> 00:20:41,105
Here's my seat.

336
00:20:43,850 --> 00:20:46,145
My feet don't touch the ground.

337
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:50,155
I feel like I'm on a trampoline.
This is awesome.

338
00:20:57,030 --> 00:21:00,099
Excuse me. Would you like anything
to drink before we take off?

339
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:02,939
- I'd like water. Lukewarm water.
- Yes, sir.

340
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:05,169
I'd like sikhye.

341
00:21:05,170 --> 00:21:08,175
I'm sorry, but we don't have sikhye.

342
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,775
Right?

343
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:12,745
Then I'd like one cold Coke, please.

344
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:14,775
I'll get one icy Coke for you.

345
00:21:27,830 --> 00:21:29,825
[ Medical Chart ]

346
00:21:31,570 --> 00:21:34,225
[ Medical Chart,
Patient Name: Park Geun-hee ]

347
00:21:40,740 --> 00:21:43,305
It's practically a bed.

348
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:46,445
What's this?

349
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,955
This is mindblowing.

350
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:13,105
- Excuse me, Ms. Flight Attendant.
- Yes, ma'am?

351
00:22:13,140 --> 00:22:15,839
- I have a favor to ask.
- Sure, what is it?

352
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:20,549
I think I might get a proposal today.

353
00:22:20,550 --> 00:22:23,075
Oh, really? Congratulations.

354
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:26,189
So I'm recording congratulatory messages
on this camera.

355
00:22:26,190 --> 00:22:28,219
Would you mind doing one for me?

356
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:29,455
Of course, ma'am.

357
00:22:31,790 --> 00:22:33,325
Okay, I'm ready.

358
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:35,925
- Cue.
- Ms. Bride-to-be...

359
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:40,165
My apologies. I'll do it again.

360
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:41,769
Cue.

361
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:43,865
Congratulations to
the groom-to-be's proposal

362
00:22:43,970 --> 00:22:46,565
and your upcoming wedding.

363
00:22:46,570 --> 00:22:49,735
Don't forget to travel with our airline
for your honeymoon.

364
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:51,605
- Wishing all the best for you two.
- Cut.

365
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:56,179
- Thank you.
- My pleasure, I envy you.

366
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:58,919
- If you need any help, please let me know.
- Okay.

367
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:01,245
Excuse me, can I get more water, please?

368
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:02,685
Yes, sir.

369
00:23:07,630 --> 00:23:08,755
Excuse me.

370
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:12,495
Sir.

371
00:23:13,830 --> 00:23:16,235
- I'd like to ask a favor.
- I can't do it.

372
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:17,565
Okay.

373
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:19,169
- But still...
- I won't do it.

374
00:23:19,170 --> 00:23:20,265
Okay.

375
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:24,505
What a snobby fellow.

376
00:23:24,950 --> 00:23:26,875
- He's got zero generosity.
- Excuse me?

377
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:32,145
What is up with this guy?

378
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:35,455
Is he a psychic or what?

379
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:48,469
[ Are you serious? ]

380
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:50,739
Yes, with the coupon event,

381
00:23:50,740 --> 00:23:53,035
you get a free upgrade
to a new sedan model.

382
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:54,665
Oh, my gosh.

383
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:57,635
Can't you see, Yeong-dong?

384
00:23:58,040 --> 00:24:01,615
The world is showering me with luck
as if I was destined to receive it.

385
00:24:02,050 --> 00:24:05,245
This Jeju trip is a bundle
of blessings over blessings.

386
00:24:06,250 --> 00:24:10,385
Awesome possum. This is amazing, blazing.

387
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:52,925
[ Medical Chart ]

388
00:24:54,870 --> 00:24:56,865
[ Medical Notes ]

389
00:25:01,740 --> 00:25:03,375
[ Lee Byeong-jin ]

390
00:25:04,580 --> 00:25:07,375
[ Would you like to have dinner together
when you come back to Seoul? ]

391
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:09,575
[ No, thanks. Help yourself. ]

392
00:25:13,850 --> 00:25:15,415
[ Lee Byeong-jin ]

393
00:25:16,290 --> 00:25:17,715
- Hey.
[ - Dr. Kim. ]

394
00:25:17,890 --> 00:25:20,089
You skip your meals most of the time
when you

395
00:25:20,090 --> 00:25:22,329
[ do diet counseling, and I'm only trying
to take care of you. ]

396
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:24,459
Why can't you just say yes
and agree to eat with me...

397
00:25:24,460 --> 00:25:26,865
I like eating alone. Okay?

398
00:25:27,430 --> 00:25:28,565
Bye.

399
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:37,505
Yeong-dong.

400
00:25:37,780 --> 00:25:41,045
I'm going to present one extravagant
birthday meal for you, okay?

401
00:25:44,350 --> 00:25:45,545
[ Pork ]

402
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:52,055
[ Silky Seaweed ]

403
00:25:53,530 --> 00:25:55,255
Should I cook him suyuk?

404
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,095
I'm getting both.

405
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:03,335
Champagne.

406
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:07,735
We can't miss drinks
on such a historic day.

407
00:26:08,780 --> 00:26:09,975
I'm getting a strong one.

408
00:26:14,850 --> 00:26:18,045
I'm sorry for having you come over
such a long way.

409
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:22,315
No, it's fine. I love Jeju Island.

410
00:26:26,590 --> 00:26:27,685
Yes.

411
00:26:37,170 --> 00:26:39,665
Well, why don't we eat first?

412
00:26:40,610 --> 00:26:42,105
- Please pick what you'd like.
- Okay.

413
00:26:52,250 --> 00:26:53,549
What should I get?

414
00:26:53,550 --> 00:26:56,085
- It's my first time to eat at this place.
- I see.

415
00:26:56,690 --> 00:27:01,029
May I take a look? This place is unique
because they use capellini pasta.

416
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:04,155
It's very thin and light.
It goes great with pasta salads.

417
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:07,329
The signature menu here is
the salmon pasta salad.

418
00:27:07,330 --> 00:27:08,695
Would you like to try that?

419
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:10,535
Sure.

420
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:13,469
[ The omega-3 fatty acids in salmon ]

421
00:27:13,470 --> 00:27:15,275
[ stimulate the brain cells. ]

422
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,179
Okay.

423
00:27:17,180 --> 00:27:19,449
[ It also increases dopamine
and serotonin, neurotransmitters ]

424
00:27:19,450 --> 00:27:21,815
[ - that control our moods. ]
- Over here.

425
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:26,015
I feel like it's all my fault.

426
00:27:26,390 --> 00:27:29,355
[ First, one's words
and actions slow down. ]

427
00:27:29,820 --> 00:27:31,855
[ It means one's thoughts
and judgments are blurred. ]

428
00:27:32,230 --> 00:27:33,585
I was weak.

429
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,225
Maybe

430
00:27:38,530 --> 00:27:40,929
I'm being punished.

431
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,995
[ Second, one may put the blame
on themselves. ]

432
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:47,235
[ One may believe all misfortunes happened
because of them. ]

433
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:59,385
[ Third, one may gather all the plates
in front of them. ]

434
00:28:00,490 --> 00:28:02,415
[ They can't afford to care for others. ]

435
00:28:05,490 --> 00:28:06,925
Other people

436
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:09,955
seem to move on after breakups.

437
00:28:11,830 --> 00:28:16,065
I feel like I'm falling into a deeper pit
as days go by.

438
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:18,965
It's really

439
00:28:21,470 --> 00:28:22,905
hard to move on.

440
00:28:27,710 --> 00:28:31,175
[ Fourth, one stops eating. ]

441
00:28:57,240 --> 00:29:00,749
Okay. I'm going in now.

442
00:29:00,750 --> 00:29:02,419
See you soon.

443
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:04,045
Gosh, I'm so nervous.

444
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:06,515
- Sung-doo.
- Hi, Producer Woo!

445
00:29:06,890 --> 00:29:08,619
- How's it going?
- I'm good.

446
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:10,655
Go in, Yeong-dong's inside.

447
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:11,815
- Okay.
- All right.

448
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:24,599
- Yeong-dong is upstairs, right?
- He's out at the moment.

449
00:29:24,600 --> 00:29:25,839
Did you call him before coming?

450
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:27,469
No. I'm here to surprise him.

451
00:29:27,470 --> 00:29:28,679
Oh, I see.

452
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:29,879
I'll wait upstairs.

453
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:32,045
Oh, we're sterilizing that floor
so you can't go now.

454
00:29:32,210 --> 00:29:33,505
Producer Woo...

455
00:29:35,620 --> 00:29:36,975
[ Stop it. ]

456
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:39,845
[ Stop what? ]

457
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:43,455
[ Stop it, it's tickly. ]

458
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:45,255
[ Are you sure? ]

459
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,025
Do... Do-hee.

460
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,395
Wait, it's her.

461
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:05,635
What?

462
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,905
You're proposing

463
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:11,905
to that passenger?

464
00:31:12,410 --> 00:31:16,279
Oh, I see you've met in advance

465
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,715
on the plane.

466
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:19,219
You said you ended things with her.

467
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:20,515
I did...

468
00:31:24,690 --> 00:31:26,555
Speak up, will you?

469
00:31:31,130 --> 00:31:32,199
You got a new action camera.

470
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:34,095
I know a friend who runs
a sole agency for these.

471
00:31:35,170 --> 00:31:36,235
Excuse me?

472
00:31:39,740 --> 00:31:42,239
You've changed your hairstyle.
It looks good on you.

473
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:43,609
It's been the same for two years.

474
00:31:43,610 --> 00:31:44,705
Is that so?

475
00:31:45,350 --> 00:31:47,509
Then, did your face change?

476
00:31:47,510 --> 00:31:49,379
Oh, maybe not that.

477
00:31:49,380 --> 00:31:50,845
You son of...

478
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:53,119
I feel like I'm the only one
trapped in this state.

479
00:31:53,120 --> 00:31:55,819
No, I feel like I'm falling into
a deeper pit.

480
00:31:55,820 --> 00:31:56,989
Everyone else seems to move on

481
00:31:56,990 --> 00:31:59,289
after a breakup
as if it was a slight cold.

482
00:31:59,290 --> 00:32:00,485
How about this?

483
00:32:00,930 --> 00:32:03,325
Think of it as a cold
that's lasting a bit longer.

484
00:32:03,500 --> 00:32:04,625
[ You! ]

485
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:12,805
Please enjoy your meals, customers.

486
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:13,935
You guys are dead.

487
00:32:14,910 --> 00:32:16,139
Enjoy your meal.

488
00:32:16,140 --> 00:32:18,209
I was going to take my time
and explain it all.

489
00:32:18,210 --> 00:32:19,475
[ "Take my time"? ]

490
00:32:19,510 --> 00:32:21,649
[ Are you evangelizing someone to church? ]

491
00:32:21,650 --> 00:32:23,419
[ How on earth were you going to explain ]

492
00:32:23,420 --> 00:32:25,145
[ that you're dumping me
because of a new girl? ]

493
00:32:28,690 --> 00:32:29,755
Hey.

494
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:33,985
Hey, don't hit me. Violence is bad.

495
00:32:34,260 --> 00:32:36,355
[ Hey, let's calm down. ]

496
00:32:46,070 --> 00:32:47,305
Goodness.

497
00:32:55,420 --> 00:32:56,545
Get up.

498
00:33:02,820 --> 00:33:04,285
[ I think I might ]

499
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:07,425
get a proposal today.

500
00:33:07,530 --> 00:33:10,695
So I'm recording congratulatory messages
on this camera.

501
00:33:12,630 --> 00:33:14,629
Hurry and get in here!

502
00:33:14,630 --> 00:33:16,035
Okay, I'll get up.

503
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:18,265
Quit your slapstick comedy acts

504
00:33:18,540 --> 00:33:20,935
- and make sure you end things right.
- Okay.

505
00:33:21,840 --> 00:33:23,235
You, shut it.

506
00:33:25,580 --> 00:33:26,609
Don't hit me.

507
00:33:26,610 --> 00:33:28,605
Aren't you going to continue
with the recording?

508
00:33:31,780 --> 00:33:33,585
It is a very crucial moment right now.

509
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:38,515
Cue.

510
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:39,755
Ms. Bride-to-be...

511
00:33:46,630 --> 00:33:47,825
Excuse me?

512
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:52,269
I can still give you
my congratulatory message.

513
00:33:52,270 --> 00:33:53,339
Please stop.

514
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:55,735
- Why that crazy wench!
- Wait! Stop!

515
00:33:57,280 --> 00:33:58,405
I mean,

516
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:01,305
you shouldn't scar
a flight attendant's face.

