You should've taken them out to dry...

782
00:54:22,520 --> 00:54:25,855
As a token of my apology,

783
00:54:26,060 --> 00:54:27,525
I got you some clothes to wear.

784
00:54:27,790 --> 00:54:28,925
Here.

785
00:54:30,700 --> 00:54:31,755
Here you go.

786
00:54:52,190 --> 00:54:55,485
Okay. I'll take that ticket.

787
00:54:56,020 --> 00:54:58,485
Thank you. Okay.

788
00:55:03,830 --> 00:55:06,625
I'm glad you can still buy a ticket.

789
00:55:10,870 --> 00:55:13,205
Are you enjoying this?
You're enjoying this now, aren't you?

790
00:55:13,410 --> 00:55:14,705
You think this is funny?

791
00:55:14,710 --> 00:55:16,035
- Well...
- Answer me.

792
00:55:17,640 --> 00:55:20,179
Were these extremely vintage clothes
really all you could find?

793
00:55:20,180 --> 00:55:21,375
I'm sorry.

794
00:55:21,380 --> 00:55:24,045
There was only one clothing store
in front of the hospital.

795
00:55:24,320 --> 00:55:25,589
Goodness.

796
00:55:25,590 --> 00:55:28,115
How am I supposed to
go to the airport like this?

797
00:55:28,450 --> 00:55:30,089
I don't have time to buy new clothes.

798
00:55:30,090 --> 00:55:32,355
Are you sure
you didn't mean to mess with me?

799
00:55:32,460 --> 00:55:33,529
No way.

800
00:55:33,530 --> 00:55:35,285
This is unbelievable.

801
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:38,295
Hey.

802
00:55:38,360 --> 00:55:41,025
I just really need to tell you this.

803
00:55:41,600 --> 00:55:44,795
You look like Kim Soo-mi

804
00:55:44,900 --> 00:55:46,665
on "Granny's Got Talent".

805
00:55:51,610 --> 00:55:53,609
Are you laughing now?

806
00:55:53,610 --> 00:55:55,979
Are you laughing
after making me look like this?

807
00:55:55,980 --> 00:55:58,249
Fine. Laugh. Keep laughing.

808
00:55:58,250 --> 00:56:00,315
They say laughing will bring you luck.

809
00:56:00,520 --> 00:56:01,685
Keep laughing.

810
00:56:05,290 --> 00:56:07,959
I'll get going. Let's end
our weird relationship here.

811
00:56:07,960 --> 00:56:09,629
Let me drive you to the airport.

812
00:56:09,630 --> 00:56:11,955
I'm good. I'll take a taxi.

813
00:56:11,960 --> 00:56:12,999
No.

814
00:56:13,000 --> 00:56:15,225
What now? What will you do now?

815
00:56:16,370 --> 00:56:17,495
What is it?

816
00:56:17,740 --> 00:56:19,135
- What is it?
- I mean...

817
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:21,365
I'm on my way to the airport anyway.

818
00:56:23,410 --> 00:56:24,939
You wouldn't let me pay

819
00:56:24,940 --> 00:56:26,875
for the hospital bill
and the flight ticket.

820
00:56:27,750 --> 00:56:31,415
Please let me do it
as a token of my apology.

821
00:56:31,750 --> 00:56:32,815
Please.

822
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:45,359
[ Then you should have called me earlier. ]

823
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:46,995
[ I thought something bad
happened to you. ]

824
00:56:47,030 --> 00:56:49,639
Why? Did you wish so?

825
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:52,239
Doctor, how did you

826
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:54,309
see me through?

827
00:56:54,310 --> 00:56:55,805
You punk.

828
00:56:56,640 --> 00:56:58,109
I'll see you when I get there.

829
00:56:58,110 --> 00:57:00,745
By the way, whose phone is this?

830
00:57:01,210 --> 00:57:02,315
What?

831
00:57:03,080 --> 00:57:06,845
Just someone I know.

832
00:57:06,950 --> 00:57:08,989
Anyway, pick me up at the airport.

833
00:57:08,990 --> 00:57:10,959
[ Okay. Have a safe trip back. ]

834
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:12,859
- Okay.
[ - Be careful not to overspeed. ]

835
00:57:12,860 --> 00:57:15,159
- Why don't you slow down?
[ - The speed limit is 80km per hour. ]

836
00:57:15,160 --> 00:57:17,125
There are no speed cameras at this time.

837
00:57:19,300 --> 00:57:20,765
[ I know this road well. ]

838
00:57:21,670 --> 00:57:23,935
Hello?

839
00:57:24,100 --> 00:57:25,335
Is that a woman?

840
00:57:26,940 --> 00:57:28,805
[ Relax Psychiatric Clinic ]

841
00:57:29,280 --> 00:57:33,275
Gosh. When I told him to go on a date,

842
00:57:33,950 --> 00:57:35,205
he said he wasn't interested,

843
00:57:35,310 --> 00:57:37,045
trying to look cool and everything.

844
00:57:37,220 --> 00:57:39,785
What a liar.

845
00:57:41,090 --> 00:57:43,055
Wait, wait!

846
00:57:45,320 --> 00:57:47,485
Watch where you're going!

847
00:57:49,360 --> 00:57:50,955
Oh, come on!

848
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:53,929
Is the brake just for decoration?
What's wrong with you?

849
00:57:53,930 --> 00:57:55,939
You're such a cowardly man.

850
00:57:55,940 --> 00:57:57,995
What a day.

851
00:58:00,070 --> 00:58:03,405
I'm not sure
if you're feeling better or worse now.

852
00:58:03,540 --> 00:58:04,775
What do you mean?

853
00:58:05,240 --> 00:58:07,905
Oh, because I was dumped by a man?

854
00:58:08,010 --> 00:58:11,075
Gosh, now I remember it.

855
00:58:11,620 --> 00:58:13,445
I don't have any regrets.

856
00:58:13,590 --> 00:58:16,315
I can find another man
when I get back to Seoul.

857
00:58:17,020 --> 00:58:20,329
There are tons of men
waiting for me out there.

858
00:58:20,330 --> 00:58:21,385
Sure.

859
00:58:21,790 --> 00:58:23,855
Good for you. I'm so jealous.

860
00:58:34,070 --> 00:58:37,135


861
00:58:51,120 --> 00:58:53,325
I wanted to send you off at the entrance.

862
00:58:53,530 --> 00:58:55,925
I'm good. It's right there.

863
00:58:56,260 --> 00:58:59,165
I'm very sorry for what happened today.

864
00:59:02,570 --> 00:59:03,735
Aren't you coming?

865
00:59:04,770 --> 00:59:06,639
I'm flying out tomorrow.

866
00:59:06,640 --> 00:59:07,735
Tomorrow?

867
00:59:08,640 --> 00:59:09,935
Then why...

868
00:59:12,680 --> 00:59:14,245
I was worried about you.

869
00:59:15,820 --> 00:59:16,945
What?

870
00:59:18,250 --> 00:59:20,745
Why does he make it sound
all so difficult?

871
00:59:20,950 --> 00:59:24,755
[ When I was at the hospital,
the doctor said... ]

872
00:59:25,520 --> 00:59:27,785
Still, you should keep an eye on him.

873
00:59:28,060 --> 00:59:29,699
He may look fine,

874
00:59:29,700 --> 00:59:33,695
but if he suddenly collapses,
he can be brain-dead.

875
00:59:42,580 --> 00:59:45,945
I would like to stay for one more day
to think more.

876
00:59:46,710 --> 00:59:50,715
I can see the lights from the airplanes
and stars here.

877
00:59:54,950 --> 00:59:56,355
They actually look quite nice.

878
00:59:56,990 --> 00:59:59,685
Then have a safe trip back to Seoul.

879
01:00:06,070 --> 01:00:07,365
Did I hear it right?

880
01:00:08,530 --> 01:00:09,895
You should eat something first.

881
01:00:10,640 --> 01:00:11,735
Bye, then.

882
01:00:25,550 --> 01:00:27,419
When something bad happens,

883
01:00:27,420 --> 01:00:29,515
most people think
they are the only unhappy ones.

884
01:00:30,090 --> 01:00:33,125
If that's what you're thinking,
please don't.

885
01:00:33,490 --> 01:00:35,185
Happiness has eyes,

886
01:00:36,660 --> 01:00:37,899
but unhappiness doesn't.

887
01:00:37,900 --> 01:00:38,995
It just chooses

888
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:42,195
anyone randomly.

889
01:01:30,580 --> 01:01:31,979
It's so pretty.

890
01:01:31,980 --> 01:01:34,715
Your boyfriend seems to have spent
quite a lot of money.

891
01:01:34,850 --> 01:01:38,215
I didn't expect to hear such big news
only after a quarter of the day.

892
01:01:38,260 --> 01:01:40,985
- Did he officially propose to you?
- Yes.

893
01:01:41,630 --> 01:01:44,429
Some obstacle butted in

894
01:01:44,430 --> 01:01:46,595
and spoiled the mood though.

895
01:01:46,900 --> 01:01:48,065
"Obstacle"?

896
01:01:48,930 --> 01:01:51,735
- What's that?
- It's a long story.

897
01:01:56,480 --> 01:01:57,675
[ Obstacle? ]

898
01:02:11,920 --> 01:02:13,425
Where should I go?

899
01:02:16,200 --> 01:02:19,125
Where should I go?

900
01:02:23,070 --> 01:02:25,165
[ Mandarin chocolate ]

901
01:02:27,870 --> 01:02:29,005
What is it?

902
01:02:29,480 --> 01:02:31,575
Mandarin chocolate.

903
01:02:31,780 --> 01:02:34,005
Buy some mandarin chocolate.

904
01:02:34,610 --> 01:02:35,775
I'm good, thanks.

905
01:02:36,980 --> 01:02:38,075
Darn it.

906
01:02:47,530 --> 01:02:48,785
[ This is the main reason. ]

907
01:02:52,300 --> 01:02:54,095
I started to hate eating with you.

908
01:02:56,500 --> 01:02:57,895
That scumbag.

909
01:03:00,640 --> 01:03:04,405
I pretended that I liked
the steak covered with pepper

910
01:03:07,080 --> 01:03:08,705
for him.

911
01:03:19,790 --> 01:03:23,095
[ This is an announcement
for passengers on Flight 908. ]

912
01:03:23,560 --> 01:03:26,395
[ The boarding gate has been changed ]

913
01:03:26,670 --> 01:03:30,865
[ from Gate 47 to Gate 43. ]

914
01:03:32,940 --> 01:03:34,605
[ Now I think about it again, ]

915
01:03:35,210 --> 01:03:38,705
I'm really sorry for what has happened.

916
01:03:42,920 --> 01:03:44,815
Today is one of the days

917
01:03:46,520 --> 01:03:47,785
when the whole universe

918
01:03:49,320 --> 01:03:52,615
is bullying me as if

919
01:03:53,290 --> 01:03:55,125
it's planned beforehand.

920
01:03:57,800 --> 01:03:59,195
On days like this,

921
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:03,035
every one of my blood vessel
in the heart hurts.

922
01:04:05,140 --> 01:04:08,065
It feels like my blood vessel is
filled with capsaicin.

923
01:04:10,580 --> 01:04:12,235
I wonder why misfortune always finds me

924
01:04:14,280 --> 01:04:16,845
every once in a while.

925
01:04:19,050 --> 01:04:21,015
[ You may say it's too much to mention ]

926
01:04:21,950 --> 01:04:23,615
[ big words like universe and heart ]

927
01:04:24,520 --> 01:04:26,955
over just a guy.

928
01:04:31,330 --> 01:04:35,595
No matter how much I loved him
and how long I have dated him,

929
01:04:38,800 --> 01:04:40,505
breaking up is heartbreaking.

930
01:04:44,680 --> 01:04:46,505
Being left alone

931
01:04:49,150 --> 01:04:50,545
hurts a lot.

932
01:05:01,790 --> 01:05:03,825
[ "Being left alone". ]

933
01:05:06,970 --> 01:05:08,125
[ It's really strange. ]

934
01:05:09,170 --> 01:05:11,235
I'm the one leaving you,

935
01:05:12,170 --> 01:05:14,905
but why do I feel like
I'm being left alone?

936
01:05:15,870 --> 01:05:19,275
Why do you
look like you haven't lost anything?

937
01:05:21,050 --> 01:05:23,275
I'm making it easier for you to leave me.

938
01:05:24,120 --> 01:05:27,745
That's not it.
You're too used to being left alone.

939
01:05:48,640 --> 01:05:50,275
[ There is no one in this world ]

940
01:05:51,410 --> 01:05:53,605
[ who is used to being left alone. ]

941
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:55,105
Next.

942
01:05:56,720 --> 01:05:58,915
[ - No one. ]
- Next.

943
01:05:59,650 --> 01:06:00,845
Next.

944
01:06:01,690 --> 01:06:03,585
Show me your ticket and ID.

945
01:06:09,930 --> 01:06:13,125
I can't go to a museum at this hour alone.

946
01:06:13,830 --> 01:06:14,995
Perch?

947
01:06:15,430 --> 01:06:17,465
I can't eat that now.

948
01:06:20,210 --> 01:06:21,765
Gosh, I'm hungry.

949
01:06:22,170 --> 01:06:24,805
Maybe I should have bought
the chocolate earlier.

950
01:06:27,250 --> 01:06:30,875
Speak of the devil.

951
01:06:35,790 --> 01:06:37,055
How much is...

952
01:06:52,570 --> 01:06:55,305
Sorry? How much is what?

953
01:06:57,680 --> 01:06:59,505
I thought you left.

954
01:07:00,810 --> 01:07:01,945
Why...

955
01:07:15,130 --> 01:07:16,325
Would you like to have

956
01:07:17,300 --> 01:07:18,525
dinner with me?

957
01:08:10,780 --> 01:08:13,793
[ Dinner Mate ]

